    <title>Overview</title>

    <para>&ws.impl.name; is a Web Services framework that provides
    tools and infrastructure to develop Web Services solutions for the end
    users and middleware developers.</para>

    <para>With &ws.impl.name;, clients and web services have a big
    advantage: the platform independence of the Java programming
    language.</para>

    <section xml:id="section-159360148062263">
        <title>Documentation</title>

        <para>This release includes the following documentation:</para>

        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para><xref linkend="jax-ws-ri-release-notes"
                xrefstyle="select:title" /></para>
            </listitem>

            <listitem>
                <para><xref linkend="users-guide"
                xrefstyle="select:title" /></para>
            </listitem>

            <listitem>
                <para><xref linkend="tools" xrefstyle="select:title" /></para>
            </listitem>

            <listitem>
                <para><link xlink:href="../javadocs/rt">API Documentation</link></para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>

        <para>The documentation/samples included with &ws.impl.name; that is
        distributed on GitHub describes how to use &ws.spec.name; to develop and
        deploy your webservices endpoints in a servlet container. The samples
        discussed in this document and available as part of &ws.impl.name;
        distribution are tested to work on GlassFish and on Apache Tomcat. The
        deployment is demonstrated using &ws.impl.name; specific proprietary
        deployment descriptor sun-jaxws.xml. </para>

        <para>If you wish to use &ws.impl.name; in a Jakarta EE container in a portable
        manner (using Jakarta Enterprise Web Services deployment descriptors), please refer to the
        <link xlink:href="https://jakarta.ee/specifications/platform/8/">Jakarta EE
        8</link> or <link
        xlink:href="https://eclipse-ee4j.github.io/glassfish/">GlassFish</link>
        documentation/samples. The majority of the documentation included with
        &ws.impl.name; is valid with Jakarta EE 8 as well.</para>
    </section>

